#speculation(title: [Brain-Derived Exosome Biomarker Panel for ME/CFS Neuroinflammation and Proteostasis])[
*Certainty: 0.35.* Exosome biomarker concept established in neurodegeneration; no ME/CFS-specific validation; isolation and characterisation methods not yet standardised for clinical use.

*Rationale.* ME/CFS involves compartmentalised CNS pathology that blood-based assays systematically miss — neuroinflammation, microglial activation, glymphatic dysfunction, and impaired proteostasis are documented by PET and CSF studies but are invisible to standard peripheral blood tests @Nakatomi2014neuroinflammation. BDEs provide a window into this compartment: neuron-derived exosomes (captured via L1CAM immunoprecipitation) can report on synaptic health (neurogranin, synaptophysin), astrocyte-derived exosomes (GFAP capture) on glial activation and AQP4 status, and microglia-derived exosomes (TMEM119 capture) on inflammatory activation state.

*Candidate cargo analytes relevant to ME/CFS:*
    - *HSP70 and ubiquitin*: Chaperone capacity and proteostasis — reduced cargo suggests impaired protein quality control @Kang2026ExosomeHSP70Sleep
    - *Inflammatory cytokines*: IL-6, TNF-α, IL-1β within exosomes reflect CNS rather than peripheral production
    - *Neuron-specific enolase (NSE) and neurogranin*: Neuronal stress and synaptic integrity
    - *α-synuclein, amyloid-β, phospho-tau*: Neurodegenerative risk markers accumulating when glymphatic clearance fails
    - *miRNA cargo*: let-7b-5p already documented as downregulated in ME/CFS EVs and correlating with fatigue

*Subtyping potential.* A multi-analyte exosome panel could address two persistent problems in ME/CFS biomarker research: (1) heterogeneity — neuroinflammatory-dominant, metabolic-dominant, and autoimmune-dominant subgroups may show distinct exosome cargo signatures, and (2) temporal dynamics — serial exosome measurements after exercise challenge could reveal CNS stress responses invisible to peripheral blood.

*Testable predictions.*
    - ME/CFS neuron-derived exosomes (L1CAM+) should show lower HSP70 and higher IL-6 cargo compared to healthy controls, with HSP70 levels correlating with cognitive symptom severity
    - Exosome cargo profiles should stratify patients into subgroups that correspond to distinct clinical phenotypes (e.g., neuroinflammatory vs metabolic vs dysautonomic)
    - Post-exertion (24--48h) exosome cargo should change in ME/CFS patients but not controls, reflecting delayed CNS stress response

*Limitations.* Certainty 0.35. BDE isolation requires specialised immunoprecipitation protocols not standardised across laboratories. L1CAM capture enriches for neuron-derived exosomes but co-isolates non-exosomal L1CAM fragments. Exosome cargo reflects a snapshot that may not capture chronic steady-state pathology. Reference ranges for healthy CNS exosome cargo across age and sex are not established. No ME/CFS BDE study has been published. The diagnostic value is unproven; the concept is derived from Alzheimer's and TBI research where BDE biomarkers have shown promise but not yet achieved clinical deployment.
] <spec:exosome-biomarker-panel>
